This paper deals with image registration using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of CNNs also suggests that this paper may fall under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves learning-based approaches, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of spatial transformer networks and thin plate spline deformation suggests that this paper may also fall under the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper involves experiments on image datasets, which suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
